The paper deals with initialization of parameters in deep neural networks, specifically in the context of convolutional neural networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of initialization on network performance, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of orthogonal matrices in recurrent networks is mentioned, which relates to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper proposes a new initialization scheme that takes into account the intrinsic structure of the convolution operator, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
